		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />When I see a high frequency, I try to relate it to known frequencies in the system. Here, 1340 kHz is one-fourth of the 5370 kHz dot clock of the NTSC NES and Super NES PPU. Are the wiggles spaced about 4 pixels apart?

		

